Description: Nine sketches; a house by a lake or river, with aboat on the water; two heads of coeckerels, separate sketches; a country in with a figure standing outside; a fishing (?) boat at sea, a net in the water, other vessels in the distance; two birds with long necks waling on a river bank; view in Egypt, with a ruined monument, a skeleton, skulls, a cannon and other objects, palm trees and pyramids in the distance; the head of a fox; a duck flying. 1830 Lithograph on grey chine collé
Producer name: Print made by: Ferdinand Philippe, duc d'Orléans
